Duckworth, meanwhile, continues to thrive at the Kazakhstani ATP 250 event and is up 30 spots to No. 108 in the PIF ATP Live Rankings. Cobolli was unable to deal with the Australian's relentless movement and pinpoint accuracy during their 91-minute clash, in which he saved all five break points he faced, according to Infosys ATP Stats.

In the top half of the draw, sixth seed Alex Michelsen rallied from a break deficit in the deciding set to defeat Shintaro Mochizuki 6-3, 3-6, 6-2 and keep alive his hopes of winning a maiden ATP Tour title.

By reaching his third tour-level semi-final of 2025, the 21-year-old American earned a 25th victory for the second straight season. He will face Corentin Moutet in Saturday's semi-final.

Moutet closed quarter-final action in Kazakhstan with a gutsy 6-4, 7-5 win over Jan-Lennard Struff. Despite dominant scoreline, the first set featured five breaks of serve, and the Frenchman was able to hold his nerve to ultimately seal a one-hour, 50-minute win.

By advancing to his his fourth ATP Tour semi-final since June, Moutet is up to his joint-career-high No. 37 in the PIF ATP Live Rankings.



